You have been given an array containing N distinct integers taken from the range 1 to N+1.
This means there is one integer missing from the range. Your task is to write a program to find and return the missing integer.

Input:

â€¢ An integer N (1 <= N <= 10^5) representing the number of elements in the array,

â€¢ N integers a1, a2, aN1 <= N+1) representing the elements of the array Each element is distinct

Input:
size of the array : 7 
 1 2 4 6 3 7 8

output : 5


Answer --- 
import java.util.Scanner;

public class MissingNumber {

    public static int findMissingNumber(int[] arr, int N) {
        // Calculate the expected sum of the first N+1 natural numbers
       int totalsum = (N+1)*(N+2)/2;
       int arraysum =0;
       for(int i=0;i<arr.length;i++){
           arraysum +=arr[i];
       }
       return totalsum - arraysum;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        
        // Input: size of the array
        int N = sc.nextInt();
        int[] arr = new int[N];
        
        // Input: elements of the array
        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            arr[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }
        
        // Find the missing number
        int missingNumber = findMissingNumber(arr, N);
        
        // Output the missing number
        System.out.println("Missing number: " + missingNumber);
        
        sc.close();
    }
}
Output --- 
7
1 2 3 4 6 7 8
Missing number: 5
